Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.71,0:00:09.41,正片中文,,0,0,0,,恐怖怪谈前情提要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Previously on Penny Dreadful...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.45,0:00:10.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她的天赋令她容易受到伤害\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Her gifts make her vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.98,0:00:13.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他们都将她变得令人垂涎\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They also make her desirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.35,0:00:14.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦内萨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Vanessa...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.62,0:00:16.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,救我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.69,0:00:17.75,正片中文,,0,0,0,,米娜怎么了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What happened to Mina?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.79,0:00:19.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她与一种生物牵扯到了一块儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}She became embroiled with a creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.59,0:00:21.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,现在她成了他的奴隶\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Now she has become his slave,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:23.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在他的世界和我们的世界之间徘徊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}hovering between our world and his.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.23,0:00:24.69,正片中文,,0,0,0,,它们全都在我身边\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They are all about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.73,0:00:26.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那你在里面做什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And what's your part in all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.43,0:00:27.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我只做我分内的事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My part is my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.83,0:00:29.43,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我有个儿子死在了非洲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I lost a son in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.47,0:00:31.67,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我的爸爸 让我跟你一起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Father mine, let me come with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.70,0:00:33.74,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我会证明自己是一个出色的冒险家\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'll prove myself a proper explorer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.77,0:00:35.57,正片中文,,0,0,0,,彼特是爱你的 爸爸\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Peter loves you, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.61,0:00:37.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.24,0:00:38.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,阿蒙内特 女孩\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Amunet, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.88,0:00:41.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不 老的那个\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No, much older.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:45.08,正片中文,,0,0,0,,阿蒙内特是太阳神阿蒙拉的配偶\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Amunet was the consort of Amun-Ra,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.12,0:00:47.12,正片中文,,0,0,0,,最初的蛇王子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}the original serpent prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.15,0:00:48.82,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他通过吸食别的灵魂\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}He was sustained by feeding
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.85,0:00:50.29,正片中文,,0,0,0,,来维持生命\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}on the souls of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.32,0:00:52.12,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不会把这些告知艾维斯夫人的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I would not tell Miss Ives this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.16,0:00:54.26,正片中文,,0,0,0,,谁想要知道他们被邪恶势力追捕\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Who wants to know they're hunted by the devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.39,0:00:56.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,发生了什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.46,0:00:57.53,正片中文,,0,0,0,,它追寻你而来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It came after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.56,0:00:58.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我认为这完全是场计谋\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I think it was all a ploy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.93,0:01:00.63,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是是米娜把我引荐给他的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But it was Mina who led me to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.66,0:01:02.20,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她可能是你的敌人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}That she may be your enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.23,0:01:03.36,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你能责怪她吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Can you blame her?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.40,0:01:04.53,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦内萨在哪\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Where's Vanessa?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.57,0:01:05.87,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我想要我的母亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I want Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.90,0:01:07.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你为什么想要她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Why do you want her?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.10,0:01:08.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,为什么每个人都想要她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Why does everyone want her?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.71,0:01:13.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,要不是我的罪过 这一切都还会发生吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But for my transgression, would any of this have occurred?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.04,0:01:15.14,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们不能改变过去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We cannot unmake the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.18,0:01:17.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们只能负罪而活 你和我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We shall live with our guilt, you and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:47.00,正片中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.58,0:03:00.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我最亲爱的米娜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My dearest Mina,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:02.38,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我亲爱的朋友\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}my darling friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.35,0:03:08.15,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我康复之后就开始写这封信\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I began these letters when I recovered from my illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.19,0:03:11.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,刚开始的时候 我大概每个月写一封\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}At first, I composed them perhaps every month.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.02,0:03:14.83,正片中文,,0,0,0,,然后每周 到现在每天\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Then weekly and now daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.93,0:03:18.43,正片中文,,0,0,0,,能确定的是 我很快就会推掉其他所有的工作\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Soon I will, no doubt, give up all other occupation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.46,0:03:20.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,只专注于写作\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and simply write.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.43,0:03:23.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一封信的结尾会成为下一封信的开头\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The ending of one letter becoming the beginning of the next,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.74,0:03:26.14,正片中文,,0,0,0,,接连着的 无止尽的文字\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}an endless ribbon of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.25,0:03:37.15,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我希望有一天你会回复我的信\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I write in hope that one day you will answer me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.18,0:03:39.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,然后一切都可以像以前一样了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and that everything can again be like it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.89,0:03:44.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,即使我知道那已不可能了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Though I know that can never be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.37,0:03:58.10,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我已经不记得我们小时候天边的云\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I don't remember clouds when we were young.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.14,0:04:01.14,正片中文,,0,0,0,,现在还有吗 我最亲爱的米娜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Were there any, my dearest Mina?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:03.87,正片中文,,0,0,0,,或许 只是在远处的地平线上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Just beyond the horizon, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.91,0:04:06.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还是 全是海岸和沙滩\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Or was it all seashore and sandcastles?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.88,0:04:09.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我知道这种想法很幼稚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Such a thought is naive, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.05,0:04:11.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是回忆不都是那样的吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But aren't memories always that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.25,0:04:14.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们再往里面跑一点 到很远很远的地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Let's go in and go terribly far out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.25,0:04:16.75,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不行 我们会被困住的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We mustn't. We'll get in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.79,0:04:18.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你害怕了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You're afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.29,0:04:21.46,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-不 我才没有 -那就跟我一起来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}-No, I'm not. -Then come in with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.49,0:04:23.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得我们能游多远\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}How far do you think we could swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.93,0:04:26.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们想游多远就多远 去到任何地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Far as we want. Everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.53,0:04:28.16,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们到那里以后要去做点什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And what would we do when we got there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:29.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,任何事都行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.53,0:04:33.33,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们应该跑到我们所能看到的地方那么远\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I think we should go in and go as far out as we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.80,0:04:36.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不 不行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No, we shouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.11,0:04:39.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你一直这么小心谨慎吗 我的米娜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Will you always be afraid, Mina mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.29,0:05:03.00,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还有比我们两家更亲近的吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Were ever two families closer than ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.03,0:05:07.20,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不记得我们两家之间的门有关上的时候\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I don't remember a day that gate between our homes was closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.24,0:05:09.72,正片中文,,0,0,0,,直到有一天它永远关上了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Until the day it closed forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.72,0:05:26.35,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你好 穆雷夫人 归家的好日子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Hello, Mrs. Murray. Gorgeous day for the homecoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.39,0:05:28.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们都在六楼和七楼\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We're all at sixes and sevens.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.12,0:05:30.06,正片中文,,0,0,0,,孩子们在阳光房里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Children are in the solarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.40,0:05:37.35,正片中文,,0,0,0,,早上好 安德鲁斯先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Good morning, Mr. Andrews.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:41.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,早上好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.97,0:05:46.54,正片中文,,0,0,0,,早上好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.57,0:05:49.23,正片中文,,0,0,0,,早上好 彼得\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Good morning, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.88,0:05:52.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,天啊 还是那只猴子吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}God, still at that monkey?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.68,0:05:54.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不管怎么试 它看起来就是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}As much as I try, it just looks...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.98,0:05:56.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-死了 -是他 不是 它\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- Dead. - He's not an "It,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.58,0:05:57.75,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他是有生命的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}he's a "He."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.78,0:05:58.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,给他取个名字吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Give him a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.99,0:06:01.02,正片中文,,0,0,0,,小瓦 他是一只愚蠢的死猴子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Van, he's a stupid dead monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.05,0:06:02.62,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你必须得给他们取名字\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You have to give them names
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.66,0:06:04.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不然他们永远不会活过来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}or they'll never come to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:07.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,它就像一位女巫的咒语\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It's like a witch's spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.70,0:06:14.90,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这里来自莎士比亚笔下的阿里尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}This is Ariel from the Shakespeare.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.93,0:06:16.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你永远\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You're forever
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.22,0:06:18.20,正片中文,,0,0,0,,都在研究吃其他物种的生物\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}working on things that eat other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.24,0:06:20.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得你很残忍\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I think you're bloodthirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.24,0:06:23.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我很残忍 她只是令人毛骨悚然\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm bloodthirsty. She's just ghoulish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.04,0:06:26.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得安德鲁斯先生有着最茂密的胡子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I think Mr. Andrews has the most luxurious mustaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.01,0:06:30.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-我知道 他棒极了 -而且还很高\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- I know, he's gorgeous. - And so tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.25,0:06:33.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我肯定会跟一个长得高的男人结婚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm sure I'll marry a tall man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:35.72,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不可能爱上一个二等残废\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I couldn't love someone stunted,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:37.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不然舞会上一定会很尴尬的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}it'd be too embarrassing at balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.59,0:06:39.82,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-他是个什么样的男人 -嗯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- What sort of man will he be? - Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.86,0:06:41.49,正片中文,,0,0,0,,至少高于六尺\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Over 6 feet at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.53,0:06:43.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,长着他每天都抹蜡的胡子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}With mustaches he waxes daily
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.93,0:06:45.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,和一双跳舞的小脚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and tiny feet for dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.53,0:06:47.90,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.93,0:06:49.87,正片中文,,0,0,0,,绝不可能是爸爸的可怕律师的一员\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Anything but one of father's dreadful solicitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.80,0:06:54.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当然 你可是要跟彼得结婚的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Then, of course, you're going to marry Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.71,0:06:57.47,正片中文,,0,0,0,,每个人都这么说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Everyone says so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.51,0:06:59.48,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不应该呆在这里跟你结婚 瓦内萨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I shan't be here to marry you, Van.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.51,0:07:00.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那你会去哪里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Where will you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.01,0:07:02.71,正片中文,,0,0,0,,去非洲跟我爸爸一起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}In Africa with father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.75,0:07:05.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你确定你想做一个探险家\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Are you sure you want to be an explorer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.08,0:07:07.48,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不可能一辈子都摆弄这些猴子标本\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Well, I can't be making stuffed monkeys my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:09.15,正片中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.60,0:07:22.17,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这些包要轻拿轻放\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Be careful with those bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.44,0:07:27.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-父亲 -你好 彼得\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- Father! - Hello, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.01,0:07:29.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,父亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.11,0:07:30.87,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-这儿是我的女孩儿们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- And there's my girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.91,0:07:32.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你们好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.58,0:07:34.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你太瘦了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You're so thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.71,0:07:36.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我都能感觉得到你的肋骨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I can feel your ribs this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.68,0:07:38.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,而且你没有戴帽子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And you haven't worn your hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.08,0:07:39.35,正片中文,,0,0,0,,噢 被你们发现了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Oh, you've caught me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.38,0:07:41.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那是我第一件弄丢的东西\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}That was the first thing I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.62,0:07:43.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-第二件是什么 -我的路\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- What was the second? - My way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:49.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你好 格拉迪斯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Hello, Gladys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:55.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,别哭了 亲爱的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}None of that, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.13,0:07:59.33,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你给我带了什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What did you bring me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.60,0:08:02.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 让我看看\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Well, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.91,0:08:04.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们有什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What have we got here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.24,0:08:06.51,正片中文,,0,0,0,,现在\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.54,0:08:09.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,呃\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.68,0:08:11.88,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-这是什么 -这是薮猫\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- What is it? - It's a serval.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.91,0:08:15.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,来自坦噶尼喀湖湖滨的薮猫\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Genus Leptailurus from the shores of Lake Tanganyika.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.28,0:08:16.78,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-好赞啊 -谢谢你 父亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- How gorgeous. - Thank you, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.82,0:08:19.39,正片中文,,0,0,0,,现在 我都快饿死了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Now, I'm as hungry as a crocodile.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.82,0:08:22.86,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你有没有准备一餐盛宴\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Have you put on a proper feast?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.41,0:08:40.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,打断一下\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.84,0:08:44.08,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我记得最清楚的就是这些归家的节日\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Those festive homecomings I remember most.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.11,0:08:46.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那才是真正的假期\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They were our true holidays.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.12,0:08:51.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我父母总是很喜欢你们一同进餐\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My mother and father were always welcome company at your table.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:57.36,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你父亲日渐晒黑 每次都会回赠我们稀有的礼物\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Your father would return to us with rare gifts and a sunburn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.39,0:08:58.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,现在 有谁乐意\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Now, would anyone like to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.73,0:09:01.03,正片中文,,0,0,0,,听听我和这些食人族待在一起的遭遇\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}hear about my encounter with the cannibals?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:03.20,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是吗 好啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes? Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.23,0:09:06.17,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但最难得的是他的探险传奇\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But rarest of all were his tales of adventure,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.20,0:09:08.20,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我相信一定润色过后才告诉我们的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm sure much edited for our ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.24,0:09:10.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当时我们突然听到一声呼喊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}...when we suddenly heard a cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.44,0:09:13.11,正片中文,,0,0,0,,尼阿美\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Nyame.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:15.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,彼得的眼睛就会亮起来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Peter's eyes would light up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.08,0:09:18.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他在想象和父亲一起会有多么非凡的未来啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Such a marvelous future he imagined alongside his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.88,0:09:20.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们还没反应过来 就被网住了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Before we knew it we were tangled up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.71,0:09:23.52,正片中文,,0,0,0,,浑身都缠着绳子和网 他们就在那儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}in ropes and nets, and there they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.55,0:09:29.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,大叫着 挥着手中的长矛 唱颂着 Nyame Nyame Nyame\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Shouting, waving their spears, chanting, "Nyame! Nyame! Nyame!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.09,0:09:31.72,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-Nyame是指肉 -噢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- Nyame means "Meat." - Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.76,0:09:35.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-新鲜的肉食 也就是我们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- Flesh. Food. Us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.16,0:09:38.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,真是可怕\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}That's just awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.94,0:09:46.14,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们开饭吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Shall we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.17,0:09:49.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,要不是我们关系这么亲密 我的米娜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But for all our kinship, my Mina,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.11,0:09:51.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们并不完全相像\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}we were not completely alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.24,0:09:53.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,天主教堂的神秘感\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The mysteries of my Catholic church
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.08,0:09:55.31,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是你和你的家人所陌生的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}were alien to you and your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.32,0:09:59.92,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我要是在大点 会看到更多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Had I been older, I would have seen more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.45,0:10:01.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在这些笑声背后\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Beneath the laughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:06.06,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在这些交谈甚欢的对话背后\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}beneath that great, easy outpouring of conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.09,0:10:08.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,其实有着紧张的暗流涌动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}it wasn't tension exactly, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.76,0:10:11.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这种感觉并不来自于双方家人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Not amongst two such congenial families.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:14.43,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.47,0:10:16.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,它更像是某种事物的颤动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It was more a tremor of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:19.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,像是声波在无底洞中传播的微弱颤抖\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Like words hollered down a bottomless pit
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.84,0:10:23.27,正片中文,,0,0,0,,回声听着会更加闷声且难以捕捉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}that come back occluded and more complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.94,0:10:25.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,也许是成长所造就的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Adulthood, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.92,0:10:41.53,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在那个恐怖的夜晚 一切发生的夜晚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And on that terrible night, that night it happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.56,0:10:44.83,正片中文,,0,0,0,,晚餐时发生过什么特别的事么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}did anything particularly important happen at the dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:47.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不 我印象中没有\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No, not that I recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.71,0:10:56.47,正片中文,,0,0,0,,老实说 我还以为\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Honestly, I thought I was going
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.48,0:10:59.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我会在下一个转角找到你和彼得\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}to find you and Peter around the next corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.08,0:11:00.71,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你们会藏在角落里吓我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}playing some trick on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.26,0:11:14.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我的母亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.46,0:11:16.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你的父亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.96,0:11:20.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,除了震惊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}More than the shock,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.70,0:11:23.83,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这种偷摸的罪恶 不堪的行为\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}the sinfulness, the forbidden act,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.13,0:11:25.63,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我看在眼里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}there was this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.90,0:11:28.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,享受其中\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.74,0:11:33.74,正片中文,,0,0,0,,好像发现了一些私语\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Something whispered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.78,0:11:35.18,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我偷偷地听着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I listened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.35,0:11:43.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,也许它一直存在着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Perhaps it has always been there, this thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.05,0:11:46.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这魔鬼就住在我体内\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}this demon inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:49.06,正片中文,,0,0,0,,或等在身后 等待我转身面对\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Or behind my back, waiting for me to turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.50,0:12:05.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我没告诉你我看到的这些\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I didn't tell you what I saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.41,0:12:07.67,正片中文,,0,0,0,,要如何启齿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}How could I?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.18,0:12:11.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,没必要让你一夜长大\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There was no need for you to grow up so fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.85,0:12:14.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-明天我们该进城了 -好啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- Tomorrow, we should go into town. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.95,0:12:19.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,其实你是可以承受的 就像我一样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You could not have endured it. Or so I told myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:24.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,也许我只是为独享这阴暗的罪恶而暗喜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Perhaps I was just cherishing the secrecy of it as a hidden sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.33,0:12:27.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但我的内心发生了变化\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But in me, there was a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.83,0:12:30.63,正片中文,,0,0,0,,从树篱迷宫那晚起 我就开始变了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I marked it from that night in the hedge maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:34.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,也许我一直就是这样的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Perhaps it was always there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.01,0:12:42.48,正片中文,,0,0,0,,做些小坏事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Little acts of wickedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.51,0:12:45.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当然是无伤大雅 所有女孩儿都会这样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Harmless, of course. Something any girl would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:48.96,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我告诉自己 我只是在淘气\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I told myself it was no more than mischief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.58,0:12:51.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,却知道 这已远超出淘气\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But I knew it was more.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:53.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我心里清楚的很\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Of course I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.69,0:13:31.36,正片中文,,0,0,0,,后来我们长大 你长得越来越可人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And as we grew up, and you grew lovelier,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:34.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,所以你先遇到真命天子也很正常\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}it was no wonder to me that you met your gentleman first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.96,0:13:37.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他有着如你期望的浓密胡须\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Or that he had luxurious mustaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.96,0:13:40.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一位英勇而年轻的军官\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Such a gallant young officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.77,0:13:42.90,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你们是如此的天作之合\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What a handsome couple you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.40,0:13:45.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,找到你啦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.48,0:13:52.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.95,0:13:58.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,彼得那时只有淡淡的胡须\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It was the season of Peter's inadequate beard,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:02.69,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我看着你和布兰森上尉的感情日益深厚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I watched your courtship with Captain Branson flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.72,0:14:05.69,正片中文,,0,0,0,,看着你们之间的爱情互动\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}All the stratagems of advance and retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.99,0:14:09.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我一直以为我是更好的那个\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I always thought of myself as the stronger one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:12.46,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但 你是这么的勇敢争取\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But here, you were so valiant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.50,0:14:14.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我又怎能不动征服之心\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}How could he not be conquered?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.43,0:14:19.47,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得你要在那张餐桌旁决定终身了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I think you set your future at that table.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.50,0:14:23.31,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他谈到印度 你突然之间就开口问道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}He spoke of India and suddenly I saw you going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.71,0:14:25.34,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我何时能再见到你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}When would I see you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:28.24,正片中文,,0,0,0,,印度不是非常遥远吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Isn't India so terribly far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:30.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那我要怎么办\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What would I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:32.15,正片中文,,0,0,0,,嫁给彼得么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Marry Peter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.35,0:14:37.49,正片中文,,0,0,0,,老天 我多么嫉妒你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}God, how I envied you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.99,0:14:41.96,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我甚至有点恨你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Perhaps I even hated you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:50.43,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你一向温柔顺从 又怎么可能\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}How was it possible that you, always so meek and obliging,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.47,0:14:53.67,正片中文,,0,0,0,,怎么可能比我先踏入婚姻的大门\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}were to have this greatest of adventures before me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.70,0:14:57.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你先去体验爱情 去体验男人的抚摸\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You would know love, you would know a man's touch,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.07,0:15:00.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,而我 一向勇敢如我 却对此一无所知\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}while I, the courageous one, knew nothing of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:04.11,正片中文,,0,0,0,,米娜乖孩子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Mina, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.09,0:15:21.00,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他是个好男人 这点毋庸置疑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Of course, he's a fine man. I've no doubt of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.03,0:15:23.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他也会是个称职的丈夫\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}He'll make a proper husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.43,0:15:24.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但我不想她远去印度\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But I hate to think of her out in India
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:28.24,正片中文,,0,0,0,,天气那么热 还有那些印度阿三\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}with all that heat and those filthy wogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.27,0:15:30.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得非洲会是什么样子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What do you think Africa will be like?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.44,0:15:33.34,正片中文,,0,0,0,,天啊 莎莎 别提了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Oh, God, Van. Don't mention that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:37.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,每次我想和父亲讨论这个问题 他就逃避\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Every time I try and talk with father about it, he shies away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.21,0:15:40.75,正片中文,,0,0,0,,也许你不该提起这个话题\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Maybe you shouldn't ask anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.78,0:15:43.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这是我的梦想 你知道的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It's all I've ever dreamed about. You know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.79,0:15:47.52,正片中文,,0,0,0,,和父亲一起探险\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My father and I off on an adventure,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.56,0:15:49.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,开拓不为人知的密道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}blazing some daring new trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.46,0:15:53.16,正片中文,,0,0,0,,或许\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.19,0:15:54.53,正片中文,,0,0,0,,或许什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.30,0:15:59.20,正片中文,,0,0,0,,或许之后 我就不会这么让他失望了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Perhaps then, I wouldn't be such a disappointment to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.04,0:16:03.27,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我从未达到过他的期望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I was never the son he wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.30,0:16:05.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,身体孱弱 不擅长游戏\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Always ill, never good at games.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.48,0:16:10.11,正片中文,,0,0,0,,总是让他失望\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}A disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.28,0:16:13.18,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他更需要一个像\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}He needed someone more like...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.21,0:16:14.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,像我一样的孩子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.38,0:16:20.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我走之后你就孤身一人了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You'll be all alone when I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.09,0:16:22.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,米娜去了印度 我和父亲远行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Mina in India, me with Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:25.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你会很难过的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}That'll be sad for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.69,0:16:27.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但我想\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.58,0:16:47.48,正片中文,,0,0,0,,牧师7点就到 母亲希望我们到场\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The minister's coming at seven and mother wants us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.85,0:16:50.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你知道她很讨厌迟到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You know how she is about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.29,0:17:01.23,正片中文,,0,0,0,,如果我能回到过去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}If I could only go back now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.26,0:17:02.96,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我会追上他 告诉他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I would run after him and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.00,0:17:04.76,正片中文,,0,0,0,,别走 别去非洲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"Don't go. Don't go to Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.80,0:17:07.17,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你会死的 身体太弱了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"You'll never survive, you're too weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.20,0:17:08.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,可你弱的那么美 彼得\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"You're beautifully weak, Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.97,0:17:11.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我爱死了你的孱弱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"I love you for your weakness."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.67,0:17:16.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,从那一刻起 米娜 我清晰地看到了未来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}For at that moment, Mina, I saw the future crystal clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.52,0:17:35.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那晚我虔诚祈祷 没等来上帝的指示\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I tried to pray that night. God didn't answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.79,0:17:38.46,正片中文,,0,0,0,,却得到魔鬼的回答\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But another did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.00,0:17:41.76,正片中文,,0,0,0,,快了 孩子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Soon, child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.87,0:17:46.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,好戏即将登场\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What games we will have.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.97,0:18:21.27,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那个周末是你最开心的时刻\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You were never happier than that weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.30,0:18:24.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,次日一早你就要举行婚礼\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}On the following morning you would be married.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.98,0:18:27.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,作为米娜 穆雷小姐 只得这一晚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}One more night as Miss Mina Murray
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.31,0:18:29.75,正片中文,,0,0,0,,明天就将成为查尔斯 布兰森夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}before you became Mrs. Charles Branson.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.78,0:18:31.11,正片中文,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.15,0:18:32.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,拜拜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Bye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.02,0:18:37.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你似乎不在意这样失去自我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You didn't seem to mind this loss of self.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.95,0:18:42.92,正片中文,,0,0,0,,可我却在意\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Perhaps I minded it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.39,0:19:22.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你找到我了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You've found me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:25.43,正片中文,,0,0,0,,最后的单身之夜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Last night of freedom, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.67,0:19:32.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你想看些有趣的事么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Would you like to see something interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.02,0:19:50.49,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.59,0:19:52.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我的米娜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My Mina?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.06,0:19:54.59,正片中文,,0,0,0,,对 你的米娜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Your Mina.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.43,0:19:56.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你不用太过惊讶\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Although you'll be relieved to know
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.63,0:19:59.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她只摆弄些温和的动物\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}she only worked with the most pacific of animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.27,0:20:03.34,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这是她的松鼠\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- This is her squirrel. -
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.91,0:20:06.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,哪些是你的？\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Which are yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:08.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,反正不是温和的动物\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Not the docile ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.24,0:20:10.34,正片中文,,0,0,0,,意料之中\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}That doesn't surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.15,0:20:18.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我总觉得想赋予一个生命\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I've always felt you have to name a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.98,0:20:20.72,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就要先给他起名\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}before it comes to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.52,0:20:23.45,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就像一个咒语\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}like a witch's spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.59,0:20:26.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他的名字是阿里尔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}His name is Ariel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.57,0:20:38.30,正片中文,,0,0,0,,最难做的部分是眼睛\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The most challenging bit is the eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:40.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,用玻璃做的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They're glass, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:43.31,正片中文,,0,0,0,,本身是没有生命的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}so by nature are dead and dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.91,0:20:46.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但捕猎者怎么能如此没有生机\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But that wouldn't do for my great predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.65,0:20:51.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,所以我在玻璃眼珠后放了镜子 就有了生气\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}So I put mirrors behind the glass eyes, so they would spark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.98,0:20:54.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,看见没\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.66,0:20:58.29,正片中文,,0,0,0,,看上去栩栩如生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It's like they're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:00.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他们就是活的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.10,0:21:09.33,正片中文,,0,0,0,,如果我可以\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I would put mirrors
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.37,0:21:11.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我想在整个世界的背后都放上镜子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}behind the entire world if I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.47,0:21:47.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.88,0:23:05.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,好了 没事的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.48,0:23:09.90,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦内莎\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Vanessa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.92,0:23:12.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦内莎 回来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Vanessa, come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.82,0:23:16.72,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-这太淫乱了 你怎么能 -我为什么不能\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- This is obscene! You mustn't! - How can I not?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.76,0:23:18.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你难道没有羞耻之心吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Have you no shame?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.46,0:23:20.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,马上给我滚上楼去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Get upstairs this instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.66,0:23:24.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你居然还有脸在我面前如此道貌岸然吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}How dare you speak to me of shame?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.73,0:23:27.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,上楼 向我父亲道歉去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Get upstairs yourself and make amends to my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.48,0:23:47.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我要见她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I have to see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.39,0:23:49.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,为了什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}To do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.49,0:23:52.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,为了解决问题\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Make this right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.70,0:24:04.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,从前 我总觉得自己浪迹天涯 远在异乡这么多年\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I always thought my traveling would kill my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.47,0:24:06.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,会害了我的家人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Being away so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.21,0:24:10.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是我太欠考虑了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My thoughtlessness...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.24,0:24:14.31,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我从没想到 会是一个可怕的小姑娘害了他们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I never imagined it would be a cruel little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.72,0:24:54.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,病症来势汹汹 无可抵挡\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}When the illness came, it was absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.72,0:24:57.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我那时几乎毫无知觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I was aware of almost nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.25,0:24:59.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,医生也无法解释发生了什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The doctors were at a loss to explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.92,0:25:02.96,正片中文,,0,0,0,,因为 你知道的 它本身就是那么的莫名\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Because, you see, it was inexplicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.68,0:25:21.78,正片中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢 谢谢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.81,0:25:23.71,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我 我来处理 我来处理\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I... I have her. I have her.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.65,0:25:33.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你必须吃点东西\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You must eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.33,0:25:43.88,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他们发现那其实并不是癫痫\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They don't think it's epilepsy anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.57,0:25:46.15,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我告诉过你了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Did I tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.41,0:25:52.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,金斯顿医生不知道要从何下手\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Dr. Kingston doesn't know what to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.94,0:25:54.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那个古怪的小个子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Ridiculous little man.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.15,0:25:58.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他们害怕\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They fear...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.95,0:26:03.47,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他们害怕的是 或许是你的大脑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They fear that, perhaps, it's your brain...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.29,0:26:07.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,有什么东西侵入了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Something inside you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.96,0:26:13.16,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还有么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What else...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.19,0:26:16.36,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还有 啊 米娜走了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}What else? Um, Mina's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.90,0:26:19.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她不想待在这儿了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}She didn't want to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.37,0:26:23.24,正片中文,,0,0,0,,大概我们不该谈论她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Should we not talk of Mina?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.41,0:26:26.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.54,0:26:31.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.68,0:26:37.62,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们不跟穆雷家的人说话 他们也不跟我们交流\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We don't talk to the Murrays, or they to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.12,0:26:42.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}我尝试过去那儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I tried going over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.12,0:26:44.02,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但他们每次都拒我于门外\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I was not welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.79,0:26:47.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,马尔 马尔科姆先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Sir Mal... Sir Malcolm...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.04,0:27:02.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,亲爱的 他们不知道你身上发生了什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They don't know what's wrong with you, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.18,0:27:08.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你的病发作时\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The seizures...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.85,0:27:11.12,正片中文,,0,0,0,,发作的时候真是太可怕了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The seizures are so terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.22,0:27:18.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们应该咨询一下伦敦的专家\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We shall be consulting a specialist in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.76,0:27:22.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你一向很喜欢伦敦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You always liked London.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.30,0:27:25.83,正片中文,,0,0,0,,所以 说不定会有所好转\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}So, perhaps the change...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.00,0:27:30.47,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们在斯特兰德大街预订了房间\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We've booked rooms at the Strand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.37,0:27:32.77,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在那里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.81,0:27:34.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在那里有一个声名远播的诊所\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There's a clinic nearby that are well known
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.87,0:27:37.31,正片中文,,0,0,0,,专为治疗女性心理失常的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}for treating women's disorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.34,0:27:38.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一个精神病院\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}An asylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.02,0:27:49.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,妈妈 我没疯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I am not mad, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.89,0:27:55.29,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不是不开心\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I am not unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.43,0:27:59.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你应该让我去死的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You should let me die.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.56,0:28:30.36,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦内萨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Vanessa,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.46,0:28:35.63,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你听懂我说的了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}do you understand what I've said?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.24,0:28:43.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得你最好待在外面 艾弗斯夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I think it best if you stepped outside, Mrs. Ives.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.97,0:28:45.17,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我哪儿也不去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'll stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.21,0:28:46.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我有些话想向你的丈夫说清楚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I must speak frankly to your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.94,0:28:48.71,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我想待在这儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'd like to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.75,0:28:51.45,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这种紧张性精神分裂 我也略有耳闻\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}This form of catatonia is not unknown to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.48,0:28:54.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这些异常的生理损耗说明\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The unusual physical exertions are manifestations of...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.35,0:28:56.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这不是正常损耗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}They were not exertions.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.09,0:28:59.35,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她在经受着折磨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}She was being tormented.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.39,0:29:01.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}我见过癫痫发作时\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I have seen epileptic seizures
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.12,0:29:02.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,能导致骨折的状况 艾弗斯夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}that have broken bones, Mrs. Ives.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.03,0:29:05.13,正片中文,,0,0,0,,并不是不可能 只是非常罕见\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}None of this impossible, just rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.00,0:29:09.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,精神性导致的癔症并非无药可医\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Hysteria of a psychosexual nature can be treated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.97,0:29:11.83,正片中文,,0,0,0,,治疗时需要用到麻醉剂\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The treatments involve narcotics
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.87,0:29:14.24,正片中文,,0,0,0,,和不断增加强度的水疗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and escalating hydrotherapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.27,0:29:17.07,正片中文,,0,0,0,,冷水将会通过减缓大脑的供血循环\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Cold water reduces circulation to the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.11,0:29:21.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,来降低新陈代谢的速度和身体的机动性\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}thereby reducing the metabolism and motor activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.08,0:29:23.48,正片中文,,0,0,0,,焦虑反应和精神创伤将会减缓\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The agitation and mental trauma will slow
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.51,0:29:24.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,最后中止\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and then cease.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.95,0:29:28.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我亲眼看到过它的疗效 艾弗斯先生 你不用有所疑虑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I've seen it work, Mr. Ives, you can have no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.08,0:29:30.78,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那如果它不起作用呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And what if it doesn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.82,0:29:32.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,如果没有起色的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}If we see no improvement,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.92,0:29:35.29,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们还可以选择进行手术\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}there are surgical options open to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.32,0:29:36.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.73,0:29:41.46,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那就这么办吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.50,0:29:44.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,艾弗斯先生 艾弗斯夫人 请即刻离开这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Mr. And Mrs. Ives, please leave the room immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.31,0:29:56.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,听到你开口真好 瓦内萨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It is very good to hear your voice, Vanessa.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.25,0:30:02.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我是克里斯朵夫 班宁医生 我是来帮你的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm Dr. Christopher Banning and I hope to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.75,0:30:03.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你的父母\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Your parents have...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.88,0:30:05.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我想离开这里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I want to be out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.59,0:30:07.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你会的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.69,0:30:09.02,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我们有一个很可爱的小花园\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We have a lovely garden that...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.06,0:30:10.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我更喜欢海洋\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I prefer the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.46,0:30:15.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你见过溺水的人吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Have you seen someone who's drowned?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.56,0:30:18.06,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我见过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.87,0:30:19.90,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不是什么猫啊狗的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Not a dog or a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.93,0:30:22.03,正片中文,,0,0,0,,它们连灵魂都没有\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Not enough soul in a dog or a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.07,0:30:23.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我是说 一个人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I mean a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.20,0:30:26.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一百个人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}A hundred men.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.17,0:30:30.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一艘奴隶贩运船\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}A slave ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.08,0:30:33.18,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是的 就是那样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes. More than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.21,0:30:36.08,正片中文,,0,0,0,,直挺挺地沉下去 而那些人们还被锁链禁锢着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Pulled right down, with the men still chained.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.12,0:30:41.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那些经受着痛苦的灵魂 如今又要忍受更重的折磨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Souls in torment who now find themselves in greater torment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.56,0:30:46.49,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你见过那个场景吗 克里斯朵夫 马修 班宁医生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Have you seen that, Dr. Christopher Matthew Banning?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.47,0:30:57.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦内萨 现在你得坐下来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Vanessa, it's very important to me that you sit down now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.58,0:31:05.18,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦内萨是谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Who's Vanessa?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.21,0:35:46.82,正片中文,,0,0,0,,艾弗斯夫人 我能进来吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Mrs. Ives, may I step in?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.12,0:35:49.38,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.25,0:35:52.75,正片中文,,0,0,0,,艾弗斯先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Mr. Ives.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.82,0:35:54.29,正片中文,,0,0,0,,皮特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.32,0:35:56.29,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我是过来道别的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I've come to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.33,0:36:00.49,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我 我将和我爸一起去非洲了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm, um, off to Africa with my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.73,0:36:05.13,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-我可以看她吗 -我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- May I see her? - I...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.17,0:36:07.04,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-可以 -并不觉得\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- Yes. - ...don't think...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.57,0:36:09.00,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在这呆着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.27,0:36:11.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.47,0:36:13.57,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你千万不要感到震惊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You mustn't be shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.61,0:36:15.38,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她改变了太多了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}She's much changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.99,0:36:27.39,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦瓦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Van...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.99,0:36:31.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,噢 瓦瓦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Oh, Van...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.80,0:36:37.56,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她会死么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Will she die?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.37,0:36:40.08,正片中文,,0,0,0,,如果上帝存在的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}If there is a God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.40,0:36:44.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她会一直这样么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Is she always like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.54,0:36:45.87,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.91,0:36:48.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,疾病还在发作\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There are episodes of activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.48,0:36:52.71,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我能过去陪陪她吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}May I sit with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.75,0:36:54.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当然可以\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.51,0:37:21.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,她还认识我吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Does she know me?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.84,0:37:25.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.71,0:37:27.88,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是和她聊聊吧 对她也是一种帮助\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But talk to her, it's meant to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.39,0:37:33.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,瓦瓦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Hello, Van.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.19,0:37:36.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我是皮特啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It's Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.82,0:37:38.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得你再近一点吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Closer, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.70,0:37:50.17,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我是皮特啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It's Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.91,0:37:55.86,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我将要去非洲了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm off to Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.64,0:38:00.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你能相信么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Can you believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.01,0:38:05.02,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我最终还是开始了这场我们说过的冒险\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Finally having that adventure we talked about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.59,0:38:09.39,正片中文,,0,0,0,,很激动啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Very excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.69,0:38:15.23,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我昨天沿着我们之前游泳的海岸\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I walked by the shore yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.26,0:38:17.16,正片中文,,0,0,0,,散步了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}where we used to swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.40,0:38:24.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你应该吻我的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You should have kissed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.81,0:38:33.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你现在会吻我吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Will you kiss me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.17,0:39:02.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你会在那儿死掉的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You're going to die there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.41,0:39:06.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你会在那儿死去的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You're going to die there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.31,0:39:43.34,正片中文,,0,0,0,,皮特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.38,0:39:45.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,祝你一路顺风\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Good luck on your trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.85,0:39:48.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢你来看她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.12,0:39:56.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,没事的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.82,0:39:58.93,正片中文,,0,0,0,,皮特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Peter,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.96,0:40:01.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他对你说了什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}what did she say to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.47,0:40:06.42,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我没听懂\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I couldn't make her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.62,0:41:07.78,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你认识济慈么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Do you know Keats?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.50,0:41:16.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那个诗人 就是那个大名鼎鼎的诗人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The poet, I mean, Keats, the poet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.40,0:41:20.14,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不能说话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I can't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.31,0:41:22.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我太虚弱了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm too weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.94,0:41:24.67,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不 你并不是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.21,0:41:30.51,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你不该在这\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You are not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.78,0:41:33.52,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.06,0:41:40.76,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你是谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.23,0:41:43.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你不是马尔科姆先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You are not Sir Malcolm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.83,0:41:46.53,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你非要给东西命名才觉得它是活的么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You have to name a thing to make it live, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.40,0:41:52.44,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那 你是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And shall I name you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.47,0:41:54.74,正片中文,,0,0,0,,除非你想让我活\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Only if you want me to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.77,0:41:56.37,正片中文,,0,0,0,,蛇\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Serpent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.31,0:41:58.68,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你是这个意思么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Is that what you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.71,0:42:02.14,正片中文,,0,0,0,,巫师 骗子 黑暗之王\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Enchanter, Deceiver, Prince of Darkness, Devil of the Pit?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.18,0:42:05.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你就这么瞧不起你的老朋友吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Have you such contempt for your old friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.32,0:42:11.02,正片中文,,0,0,0,,继续 济慈\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}So, the Keats...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.05,0:42:13.16,正片中文,,0,0,0,,夜莺颂里面有这四句话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Four lines from Ode to a Nightingale
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.19,0:42:15.79,正片中文,,0,0,0,,总能和我达到共鸣\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}have always struck a chord with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.56,0:42:18.73,正片中文,,0,0,0,,当济慈写这诗的时候 他濒临死亡\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Keats was dying when he wrote them,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.76,0:42:19.86,正片中文,,0,0,0,,而且 他知道他即将死去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and he knew he was dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.90,0:42:23.13,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你不觉得这为诗增加了趣味吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}which adds to the piquancy, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.80,0:42:26.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你要听这四句话吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Would you like to hear them?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.07,0:42:28.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我没得选好吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Do I have a choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.54,0:42:29.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,听好了 瓦纳萨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Vanessa, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.64,0:42:32.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你永远都是有选择的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You've always had a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.64,0:42:35.18,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你允许这一切发生的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You allowed all this to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.21,0:42:38.78,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你找到了它又毁了它\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Hell, you sought it out and fucked it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.58,0:42:44.82,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你可以随时关上门\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You could have shut the door at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.85,0:42:46.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你随时可以\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.72,0:42:49.06,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就现在 你会吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Right now. Will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.76,0:42:54.19,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.23,0:42:57.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还要放弃一切我们会拥有的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And give up everything we could have together?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.73,0:43:01.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一个人最美好但是也是最罪恶的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The true knowledge of man's virtue, as well as his sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.24,0:43:03.75,正片中文,,0,0,0,,就是权力\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The power.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.94,0:43:07.11,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这个世界之外的风景\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The sight beyond this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.14,0:43:09.41,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我对这世界之外别无所求\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I want nothing beyond this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.44,0:43:11.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不要撒谎了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Don't lie to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.35,0:43:17.35,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你一直沉溺于深海\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You've always been drawn to the deep ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.92,0:43:21.12,正片中文,,0,0,0,,陶醉在黑暗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}to the dark whisper,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.06,0:43:25.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,玻璃眼背后的镜子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}a mirror behind the glass eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.53,0:43:31.26,正片中文,,0,0,0,,生命最完整的状态\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}To life at its fullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.57,0:43:34.77,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你能现在关门么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Will you close that door now?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.10,0:43:39.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 继续\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}So, the Keats.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.94,0:43:42.38,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那四句话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The lines from Keats.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.41,0:43:43.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,听着在\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.64,0:43:47.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我在黑暗中倾听\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"Darkling, I listen
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.32,0:43:50.92,正片中文,,0,0,0,,多少次\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"And, for many a time I
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.92,0:43:53.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我几乎爱上了静谧的死亡\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}have been half in love with easeful Death,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.26,0:43:58.26,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我在诗思里用尽了我的言辞\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"Call'd him soft names in many a mused rhyme
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.29,0:44:04.13,正片中文,,0,0,0,,求他把我的一息散入空茫\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}"To take into the air my quiet breath."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.84,0:44:20.41,正片中文,,0,0,0,,所以 黑暗回答了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}So the darkness spoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.81,0:44:22.28,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.05,0:44:27.08,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你还听到了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But you listened.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.87,0:45:16.23,正片中文,,0,0,0,,愿克莱尔 艾夫斯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}May the soul of Claire Ives
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.27,0:45:18.40,正片中文,,0,0,0,,和其他忠诚的灵魂\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and the souls of all the faithful
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.44,0:45:20.64,正片中文,,0,0,0,,受到上帝的仁慈庇佑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}departed through the mercy of God
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.67,0:45:21.97,正片中文,,0,0,0,,永保安息\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.01,0:45:24.57,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-阿门 -阿门\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- Amen. - Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.28,0:46:35.88,正片中文,,0,0,0,,妹妹\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.21,0:46:40.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不怪你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I do not blame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.85,0:46:43.32,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不管是什么样的罪行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Whatever sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.35,0:46:45.82,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在你的苦难折磨中都慢慢会被原谅\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}it has been forgiven in your suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.32,0:46:50.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在如此痛苦的折磨下\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}So much suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.46,0:46:54.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我受到的折磨比我应得的还多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It is more than I deserve,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.63,0:46:57.86,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但我仍然不能原谅我自己\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}but I can't forgive myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.30,0:47:00.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,想说的太多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There's so much to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.64,0:47:02.23,正片中文,,0,0,0,,或者太少\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Or so little.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.21,0:47:10.51,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我现在结婚了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm married now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.54,0:47:12.45,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你能想象吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Can you imagine that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.15,0:47:15.45,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他是个律师\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}He's a lawyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.48,0:47:18.02,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在埃塞克斯的霍金斯手下工作\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}in the employ of Mr. Hawkins of Essex.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.99,0:47:21.05,正片中文,,0,0,0,,他并没有像我英勇的布兰森队长\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}He doesn't have a mustache
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.09,0:47:23.76,正片中文,,0,0,0,,一样有小胡子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}like my gallant Captain Branson,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.79,0:47:28.63,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是哈克先生是个好人他也深爱着我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}but Mr. Harker's a good man and he loves me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.47,0:47:38.20,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我为你感到高兴\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm happy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.21,0:47:42.94,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还有我们可怜的皮特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And our poor Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.58,0:47:45.08,正片中文,,0,0,0,,很抱歉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.11,0:47:47.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,要是你那天在迷宫里面去追他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}If only you had run after him that day in the maze,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.72,0:47:53.35,正片中文,,0,0,0,,然后抱紧他并告诉他不要去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and held him tight, and told him not to go
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.39,0:47:55.90,正片中文,,0,0,0,,而且你告诉他你就爱他的孱弱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and that you loved him for his weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.26,0:47:58.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你是怎么知道的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}How do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.39,0:48:03.96,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我现在知道很多事了瓦内萨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I know about many things now, Vanessa.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.36,0:48:07.80,正片中文,,0,0,0,,主告诉我了许多事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}The master has taught me much.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.50,0:48:13.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那些没人应该知道的事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Things no one should ever know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.71,0:48:15.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,救救我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.94,0:48:19.71,正片中文,,0,0,0,,把我从头手中就走\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Save me from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.81,0:48:20.91,正片中文,,0,0,0,,求求你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.60,0:49:15.46,正片中文,,0,0,0,,米娜需要我们的帮忙\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Mina needs our help.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.67,0:49:18.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,先让我进去可以吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Will you let me in?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.67,0:49:25.21,正片中文,,0,0,0,,还有其他事儿吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And there's nothing more?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.24,0:49:26.54,正片中文,,0,0,0,,没了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.54,0:49:31.45,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你认为你还能再接近她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You believe you can reach out to her again?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.48,0:49:33.15,正片中文,,0,0,0,,或者是她接近我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Or she to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.72,0:49:36.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我知道你不相信\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I know you do not credit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.58,0:49:38.55,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你可不了解我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You know nothing of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.86,0:49:49.03,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你知道我杀过多少人吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Do you know how many men I've killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.06,0:49:52.37,正片中文,,0,0,0,,在非洲我们每一步都踏在血上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}In Africa we walked in blood every step.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.54,0:49:57.00,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我曾一度很想杀了你以解心头只恨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There was a time I would gladly have killed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.31,0:50:01.46,正片中文,,0,0,0,,也许终有一天我会真的杀了你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There may come a time when I gladly shall.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.98,0:50:06.65,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是现在来看 我可以好好利用你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But for now, I can make use of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.21,0:50:09.45,正片中文,,0,0,0,,-没有了吗 -还有什么吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}- And no more? - What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.48,0:50:11.35,正片中文,,0,0,0,,宽恕\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Forgiveness?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.22,0:50:16.96,正片中文,,0,0,0,,去你的罗马教堂去找吧 最后你会在那一无所获\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Go to your Roman church for that, you'll find none here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.60,0:50:26.50,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你是否真正的想象过一分钟\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Have you imagined for one moment
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.53,0:50:28.60,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这对我来说是什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}what this has been for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.57,0:50:35.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,不可被原谅的罪行已经在我的一生中留下了不可磨灭的记号\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}An unforgivable transgression that has marked me for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.64,0:50:37.74,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你认为你在痛苦中煎熬\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You think you've suffered.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.78,0:50:39.98,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你认为你在刀尖上嗜血\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You think you know blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.01,0:50:42.95,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你认为你在生死中浮沉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You think you've walked on corpses.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.98,0:50:47.52,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你将这些丑陋之事隐匿 可我却比你遭受的更多\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Spread them from here to the horizon and I have walked further!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.62,0:50:52.66,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你这个软弱 肮脏 好色还有虚荣的男人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You weak, foul, lustful, vainglorious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.69,0:50:55.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你怎么胆敢擅自跟我聊到死亡\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}How dare you presume to speak to me of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.93,0:51:01.43,正片中文,,0,0,0,,那我们应该一起谈谈\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Then we shall speak of it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.27,0:51:09.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.84,0:51:12.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我就跟着它找到米娜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}We will follow it to Mina.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.01,0:51:16.48,正片中文,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.12,0:51:18.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,接下来呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.52,0:51:21.09,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你大限将至\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}You will be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.12,0:51:22.85,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我继续前行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I will walk on.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.86,0:51:30.49,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我会让塞姆班准备一个房间的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I'll have Sembene prepare a room.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.70,0:51:34.10,正片中文,,0,0,0,,这就是你的家了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}This is your home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.64,0:51:44.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我不期望你对我宽恕\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There is no exculpation I expect of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.04,0:51:47.61,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我的内疚终是我的 我将与它同行\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}My guilt is my own and that I carry with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.98,0:51:51.01,正片中文,,0,0,0,,它便是我的现在与将来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It is my present and my future.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.05,0:51:54.58,正片中文,,0,0,0,,它已经使我如此短暂的人生糟糕透顶\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}It has damned me well beyond this short life of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.92,0:52:02.89,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是在确保你安全之前我将不永不停息\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But I will not rest until you are safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.26,0:52:06.96,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我人生将再无其他追求\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}There is no other purpose in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.63,0:52:12.84,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我永远爱你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I shall love you always.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.87,0:52:15.70,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你最亲爱的朋友 瓦内萨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Your dearest friend, Vanessa.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.41,0:53:32.11,正片中文,,0,0,0,,附言\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Postscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.15,0:53:33.81,正片中文,,0,0,0,,你的父亲很爱你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}Your father loves you very much
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.85,0:53:36.45,正片中文,,0,0,0,,愿意做一切来拯救你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}and would do anything to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.35,0:53:39.25,正片中文,,0,0,0,,但是我对你是另一种哎\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}But I love you in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.56,0:53:44.22,正片中文,,0,0,0,,我爱你爱到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}I love you enough
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.96,0:53:45.99,正片中文,,0,0,0,,可以杀了你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs30}to kill you.
